label.value: prestalk AB core region of the mid culminant

value.value: Cone-shaped area of the prestalk zone of the mid culminant that occupies a core among the pstA region. Cells of the pstAB region express both the ecmA and ecmB genes.

label.value: stalk of the mid culminant

value.value: Tubular structure of the mid culminant that consists of cellulose-covered cells stacked on top of each other and surrounded by an acellular stalk tube composed of cellulose and glycoprotein.

definition.value: Synonym from Kessin book p. 12-13; Kessin book p. 193.

label.value: stalk tube of the mid culminant

value.value: Open, cylindrical tube of the mid culminant composed of cellulose and glycoprotein and surrounded by a ring of actin in which stalk cells accumulate.

label.value: prespore region of the mid culminant

value.value: Region of the mid culminant mostly composed of prespore cells. In addition to prespore cells, the prespore region contains anterior-like cells (ALC) that express ecmA and/or ecmB. The prespore region occupies about three quarters of the organism.

label.value: upper cup region of the mid culminant

value.value: Region of the prespore zone of the mid culminant that borders the prestalk region.

label.value: prespore/base region of the mid culminant

value.value: Region of the prespore zone of the mid culminant that borders the base.

label.value: basal disc of the mid culminant

value.value: Region located of the mid culminant located closest to the substratum and composed of pst cells (rearguard cells).

label.value: peripheral layer of the mid culminant

value.value: Layer surrounding the mid culminant and composed of an electron-dense cell type.

label.value: stalk of the late culminant

value.value: Tubular structure of the late culminant that consists of cellulose-covered cells stacked on top of each other and surrounded by an acellular stalk tube composed of cellulose and glycoprotein.

definition.value: Synonym from Kessin book p. 12-13, Kessin book p. 193.

label.value: stalk tube of the late culminant

value.value: Open, cylindrical tube of the late culminant composed of cellulose and glycoprotein and surrounded by a ring of actin in which stalk cells accumulate.

label.value: sorus of the late culminant

value.value: Ovoid structure of the late culminant supported by the stalk and that contains the spores.

label.value: apical disc of the late culminant

value.value: Most apical structure of the late culminant. Composed of cells that express the prestalk markers ecmA, ecmB and staB.

label.value: upper cup of the late culminant

value.value: Region of the late culminant located above the spore mass and composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: lower cup of the late culminant

value.value: Region of the sorus of the late culminant located at the base of the sorus and composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: basal disc of the late culminant

value.value: Conical-shaped structure of the late culminant that anchors the stalk to the substratum. Composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: inner basal disc of the late culminant

value.value: Central portion of the basal disc of the late culminant. Composed of stalk cells.

label.value: outer basal disc of the late culminant

value.value: Ring of cells at the periphery of the basal disc of the late culminant. Composed of pstB cells (rearguard cells) and other anterior-like cells.

label.value: stalk of the fruiting body

value.value: Tubular structure of the fruiting body that consists of cellulose-covered cells stacked on top of each other and surrounded by an acellular stalk tube composed of cellulose and glycoprotein. The stalk of the mature fruiting body is usually 5-15 microns in diameter and between 1.5 to 3 cm in height.

label.value: stalk tube of the fruiting body

value.value: Open, cylindrical tube of the fruiting body composed of cellulose and glycoprotein and surrounded by a ring of actin in which stalk cells accumulate.

label.value: sorus of the fruiting body

value.value: Structure of the fruiting body supported by the stalk and that contains the spores. The sorus is 125-300 microns in diameter, lemon-shaped, and grayish white to pale yellow in color.

label.value: apical disc of the fruiting body

value.value: Region of the fruiting body located above the spore mass and composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: lower cup of the fruiting body

value.value: Region of the fruiting body located at the base of the sorus and composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: basal disc of the fruiting body

value.value: Conical-shaped structure of the fruiting body that anchors the stalk to the substratum, around 150 to 400 microns in diameter. Composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: inner basal disc of the fruiting body

value.value: Central portion of the basal disc of the fruiting body composed of stalk cells.

label.value: outer basal disc of the fruiting body

value.value: Ring of cells at the periphery of the basal disc of the fruiting body composed of pstB cells (rearguard cells) and other anterior-like cells.

label.value: slime trail

value.value: Acellular material from the surface sheath left behind the migratory slug as it moves. Can be up to 2-3 cm in length.

label.value: surface sheath of the mid culminant

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins. Covers the basal disc of the mid culminant.

label.value: surface sheath of the late culminant

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins. In the late culminant, covers only the basal disc.

label.value: surface sheath of the fruiting body

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins. In the fruiting body, covers only the basal disc.

label.value: tip-organizer of the tipped mound

value.value: Part of the prestalk region of the tipped mound that acts as an organizer, that is, a signalling center that directs the morphological characteristics of the entire organism.

label.value: Dictyostelium discoideum single cell organism

value.value: Cell that is an individual member of the species Dictyostelium discoideum.

label.value: macrocyst

value.value: Unicellular diploid organism resulting from the fusion of two cells of opposite mating types.

label.value: prespore region

value.value: Region mostly composed of prespore cells. In addition to prespore cells, the prespore region contains anterior-like cells (ALC) that express ecmA and/or ecmB. The prespore region occupies about three quarters of the organism.

label.value: prestalk region

value.value: The prestalk region is located at the most apical part of the organism. It consists of about one quarter of the cells.

label.value: prestalk A region

value.value: Anterior-most region of the prestalk zone characterized by high expression of the ecmA gene directed by the proximal part of its promoter (ecmA promoter).

label.value: basal disc

value.value: Conical-shaped structure that anchors the stalk to the substratum. Composed of anterior-like cells.

label.value: peripheral layer

value.value: Layer surrounding the pseudoplasmodium and composed of an electron-dense cell type.

label.value: prestalk AB core region

value.value: Cone-shaped area of the prestalk zone that occupies a core among the pstA region. Cells of the pstAB region express both the ecmA and ecmB genes.

label.value: prestalk O region

value.value: Area of the prestalk zone located posterior to the pstA region and characterized by low expression of the ecmA gene directed by the distal part of its promoter (ecmO promoter).

label.value: stalk

value.value: Tubular structure that consists of cellulose-covered cells stacked on top of each other and surrounded by an acellular stalk tube composed of cellulose and glycoprotein.

label.value: sorus

value.value: Ovoid structure supported by the stalk and that contains the spores.

label.value: peripheral layer cell

value.value: Electron-dense cell connected to neighboring peripheral layer cells thus forming a coherent tissue around the multicellular organism.

definition.value:
Characterisation of an epithelium-like layer of cells in the multicellular Dictyostelium discoideum slug. 
M Fuchs, MK Jones, KL Williams - Journal of Cell Science, 1993. ISSN:0021-9533.
not indexed in PubMed.

label.value: surface sheath

value.value: Acellular material composed of polysaccharides and proteins, formed during late aggregation and that holds the cell mass together throuhout development.

label.value: stalk tube

value.value: Open, cylindrical tube that appears during culmination. The stalk tube is composed of cellulose and glycoprotein and surrounded by a ring of actin in which stalk cells accumulate.

label.value: inner basal disc

value.value: Central portion of the basal disc. Composed of stalk cells.

label.value: outer basal disc

value.value: Ring of cells at the periphery of the basal disc composed of pstB cells (rearguard cells) and other anterior-like cells.

label.value: prestalk A region of the tipped mound

value.value: Anterior-most region of the prestalk zone of the tipped mound characterized by high expression of the ecmA gene directed by the proximal part of its promoter (ecmA promoter).

label.value: prestalk AB core region of the tipped mound

value.value: Cone-shaped area of the prestalk zone of the tipped mound that occupies a core among the pstA region. Cells of the pstAB region express both the ecmA and ecmB genes.

label.value: prestalk O region of the tipped mound

value.value: Area of the prestalk zone of the tipped mound located posterior to the pstA region and characterized by low expression of the ecmA gene directed by the distal part of its promoter (ecmO promoter).

label.value: tip-organizer

value.value: Part of the prestalk region that acts as an organizer, that is, a signalling center that directs the morphological characteristics of the entire organism.
